 relevant to grading, and whether heavy reliance on anonymous student evaluations of teaching excellence has a distorting effect on grading practices. Finally, the contributors offer contrasting perspectives on the prospects for reform.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEducation, HigherxStandardszUnited States. 0aGrading and marking (Students)zUnited States. 4aEducation : Education Policy and Leadership. 4aEducation : Educational Administration. 4aEducation : Educational Psychology. 4aEducation : Higher Education. 4aEducation : Philosophy of Education. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh1 aAdelman, Clifford, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeito, David T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBiggs, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrighouse, Harry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHunt, Lester H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHunt, Lester H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKamber, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKohn, Alfie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNuckolls, Charles W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchrag, Francis K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079147800440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791478004423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791478004/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles